==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|haineus||lang=fro}} (compare French {{term|haineux|lang=fr}}) from {{term|hair||to hate|lang=fro}}, of {{etyl|gem}} origin.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈheɪnəs/|/ˈhiːnəs/}}
*: {{audio|en-uk-heinous.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
*: {{audio|en-us-heinous.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|eɪnəs}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|more}}

# Totally [[reprehensible]].
#: ''I hope they catch the person responsible for that '''heinous''' crime.''

====Usage notes====
* Nouns to which "heinous" is often applied: crime, act, sin, murder, offence.

